# .NET Assignment – Build .NET Applications with C#

## Overview

This project was developed as part of the Microsoft Learn modules for building .NET applications using C#. It includes:

* A RESTful Web API using ASP.NET Core (CRUD operations)
* A file processing application that generates a sales summary report

---

## Part 1 – Web API (Pizza API)

### Description

A simple ASP.NET Core Web API that manages a list of pizzas and supports full CRUD operations.

### Added Record (Requirement)

An additional pizza was added to the list:

* **Id:** 3
* **Name:** Calabresa

---

### Endpoints and Test Results

#### GET /pizzas

* **Description:** Retrieve all pizzas
* **Status Code:** 200 OK

#### POST /pizzas

* **Description:** Create a new pizza
* **Example Request Body:**

```json
{
  "name": "Chicken"
}
```

* **Status Code:** 201 Created

#### PUT /pizzas/{id}

* **Description:** Update an existing pizza
* **Status Code:** 204 No Content

#### DELETE /pizzas/{id}

* **Description:** Delete a pizza
* **Status Code:** 204 No Content

---

## Part 2 – File and Directory Processing

### Description

A console application that reads multiple `.txt` files containing sales data and generates a summary report.

---

### Sales Summary Function

```csharp
using System.Text;

public class SalesReport
{
    public static void GenerateSalesReport(string directoryPath)
    {
        var files = Directory.GetFiles(directoryPath, "*.txt");
        decimal totalSales = 0;
        var report = new StringBuilder();

        report.AppendLine("Sales Summary");
        report.AppendLine("----------------------------");

        var details = new List<string>();

        foreach (var file in files)
        {
            decimal fileTotal = 0;

            foreach (var line in File.ReadAllLines(file))
            {
                if (decimal.TryParse(line, out decimal value))
                {
                    fileTotal += value;
                }
            }

            totalSales += fileTotal;
            details.Add($"{Path.GetFileName(file)}: {fileTotal:C}");
        }

        report.AppendLine($"Total Sales: {totalSales:C}");
        report.AppendLine("\nDetails:");

        foreach (var detail in details)
        {
            report.AppendLine(detail);
        }

        File.WriteAllText(Path.Combine(directoryPath, "SalesSummary.txt"), report.ToString());
    }
}
```

---

### Example Output

```
Sales Summary
----------------------------
Total Sales: $3,500.00

Details:
file1.txt: $1,000.00
file2.txt: $2,500.00
```

